ücken Fragen der Bewohnbarkeit und Gastfreundschaft in den Vordergrund - und die Schaffung neuen Wissens bedeutet stets auch die Schaffung neuer Welten. Dieses Buch spricht alle mit dem Universum und dem Menschen befassten Wissenschaften an.  aThinking planetary means taking the Earth seriously as a planet: from the Earth's core to interplanetary space, from the nanosecond to deep time, from elementary particles to the Earth's mass. If the focus is on interactions between our home planet and ourselves, a planetary knowledge paradigm takes shape. It goes hand in hand with the relationalisation of human existence in the universe and the relativisation of the anthropocentric view. Thus, questions of habitability and hospitality come to the fore and the creation of new knowledge always means the creation of new worlds. This book addresses all sciences concerned with the universe and human beings.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aEinführung. 4aErdsystem. 4aKultur. 4aMenschheit. 4aNachhaltigkeit. 4aNatur. 4aNaturphilosophie. 4aPlanet. 4aPolitik. 4aSoziologie. 4aUmwelt. 4aUmweltpolitik. 4aUmweltsoziologie. 4aUniversität. 4aWissen. 4aÖkologie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aCulture.  aEarth System.  aEcology.  aEnvironment.  aEnvironmental Policy.  aEnvironmental Sociology.  aHumanity.  aIntroduction.  aKnowledge.  aNature.  aPhilosophy of Nature.  aPolitics.  aSociology.  aSustainability.  aUniversity.1 aLeggewie, Claus, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMeyer, Erik, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-D